#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:5
msgid ""
"ADCToolbox is organized around Python modules that map to common ADC "
"analysis workflows: generate or import data, analyze analog or digital "
"output, calibrate weights when needed, and build plots or dashboards from "
"the results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:9
msgid "Python Package Layout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:25
msgid ""
"The top-level package exports the most common functions through "
"`adctoolbox.__init__`, while submodules remain available for explicit "
"imports such as `from adctoolbox.models import sar_convert`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:29
msgid "Common Data Paths"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:41
msgid ""
"This path is used for SNDR/SNR/SFDR/ENOB measurement, residual statistics, "
"static nonlinearity fitting, phase-plane views, and dashboard generation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:54
msgid ""
"This path is used for SAR and bit-weighted ADC debug. Calibration and "
"application are separate steps: calibration estimates the true bit weights, "
"and normal operation reconstructs output with those calibrated weights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:58
msgid "SAR Behavioral Modeling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:69
msgid ""
"The SAR model supports binary or redundant weights, explicit quantization "
"ranges, sampling noise, comparator noise, and capacitor mismatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:72
msgid "Time-Interleaved ADC Analysis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:83
msgid ""
"The TI-ADC utilities focus on offset, gain, and timing-skew mismatch for "
"sine captures. Fractional-delay helpers are provided for correction "
"workflows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:86
msgid "Examples And Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:88
msgid ""
"The packaged examples are the canonical runnable workflows. Copy them with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:94
msgid ""
"The example tree currently contains 59 scripts across spectrum analysis, "
"signal generation, analog debug, digital/SAR calibration, toolset "
"dashboards, conversions, time-interleaving, and downsampling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/algorithms/AlgorithmOverview.md:98
msgid "Maintenance Notes"
msgstr ""

